  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Engine removal and installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Fuel feed tube must be removed after releasing fuel pressure.",
        "Fire is strictly prohibited.",
        "If the radiator cap is removed when the water temperature is high, the coolant is under pressure and may spurt out. After the water temperature drops, wrap the cap with a piece of cloth and open it gently.",
        "Garage jacks, rigid racks, hanger hooks, and lifts should be securely hung in place.",
        "For safety reasons, the removed wheels should be placed under the side sills behind the rigid rack.",
        "The rear wheels must have parking brakes and wheel stops must be used."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Use fender covers and do not scratch painted surfaces.",
        "Wires should be disconnected gently by holding the coupler and connector section to prevent disconnection during removal.",
        "When installing wiring and hoses, be careful not to connect them incorrectly. Also, make sure that wiring and hoses do not become entangled or interfere with other parts.",
        "Do not allow coolant to adhere to electrical components or painted surfaces. If it does adhere, wipe it off immediately.",
        "Waste oil, parts cleaning oil, etc. after oil (or fluid) change should be disposed of in accordance with laws, regulations, ordinances, etc."
      ]
    },
