    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582683_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the A/C pipe clamp bolt (A). Remove the harness clamp (B) on the A/C compressor. Remove the A/C pipe from the clamp (C)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "31. A/C compressor removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582684_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the A/C compressor."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not disconnect the suction and discharge hoses.",
        "The removed compressor should be hung by a rope or other means."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "32. Disconnect Upper Hose/Lower Hose/Heater Hose"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582685_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582686_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Disconnect the upper hose (A), lower hose (B) and heater hose (C) and remove from the hose clamp (D)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "33. Remove control wires",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000553",
          "label": "Remove control wires",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "34. Master Power Tube Disconnect"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582687_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Disconnect master power tube (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "35. Relay box power cable Disconnect"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582688_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Disconnect the power cable (B) from the relay box (A). Disconnect the coupler (C). Remove the relay box (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "36. リレー ボックス ステイ 取外し"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582689_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Disconnect the coupler (A). Remove the harness clamp (B). Remove the A/C tube clamp (C). Remove the relay box stay (D)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "37. Lift Up"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Raise the car body using a lift."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "38. Torque rod removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Place a plate over the transmission and support it with a transmission jack, and remove the torque rod. Remove the transmission jack.",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000359",
          "label": "Place a plate over the transmission and support it with a transmission jack, and remove the torque rod.",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "When removing the transmission jack, lower it gradually as the engine moves forward."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "39. Subframe removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582690_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Support the sub-frame (A) with a transmission jack (B) using a square timber or similar. Remove the sub-frame mounting bolt (C). Remove the underload pass rod mounting bolt (D). Remove the sub-frame."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "40. Engine Removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582691_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Lower the vehicle body until the engine and transmission hit the workbench with about 20 mm of square wood under the transmission and 55 mm under the oil pan."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "The worktable shall have a load capacity of 600Kg or more."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582692_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Remove the side engine mount bracket mounting nut."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582693_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Remove the transmission mount bracket mounting bolts/nuts."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not get under the body of the vehicle when it is raised."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "When tightening engine mount-related bolts/nuts, observe the steps to prevent noise and vibration and to maintain the durability of the bushings."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Engine Temporary tightening"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582694_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Place a square piece of wood about 20 mm under the transmission and 55 mm under the oil pan, and place the engine assembly on the workbench."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "The worktable shall have a load capacity of 600Kg or more."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not get under the body of the vehicle when it is raised."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582695_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Temporarily tighten the new side engine mount bracket mounting nut (A) and loosen the side engine mount bracket mounting bolt (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582696_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "4",
      "text": "Temporarily tighten the new transmission mount bracket mounting bolt/nut (A) and loosen the transmission mount bracket mounting bolt (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Lift Up"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Sub-frame Temporary tightening"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582697_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Support the sub-frame (A) with the transmission jack (B) using a square timber, etc., and lift it up to the body. Temporarily tighten the new subframe mounting bolts (C). Temporarily tighten the underload pass rod mounting bolt (D). Remove the transmission jack."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Subframe Tightening",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000865",
          "label": "Subframe Tightening",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Anda Load Path Rod Tightening",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000864",
          "label": "Anda Load Path Rod Tightening",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "6. Torque Rod Mounting"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582698_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Lay a plate on the transmission and support it with a transmission jack. Temporarily tighten the new mounting bolts (D). Remove the transmission jack."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Install the torque rod and tighten the new mounting nut (A). When installing the bolt on the front sub-frame side, align the non-turn plate (B) of the bolt with the notch (C) in the guide section of the front sub-frame, insert the bolt, and install the nut."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "7. Lift Down"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "8. Tighten side engine mount brackets."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582699_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Tighten the side engine mount bracket mounting bolts/nuts in the order of their numbers."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "9. Transmission Mount Bracket Tightening"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582700_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Tighten the transmission mount bracket mounting bolts/nuts in numerical order."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "10. Lift Up"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "11. Torque Rod Tightening"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "356_3.0_jpn_11582701_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
